SUMMARY:Yoga Vinyasa Krama 
DESCRIPTION:Nataraja School of Traditional Yoga\n**Yoga Vinyasa Krama - Th
 ursdays 9-10:30am**\n**Songbird Community Healing Center Cotati**\n**RSVP 
 ONLY**\nExperience physical health & fitness\, pranic flow\, vital energy 
 & stillness - through intelligent architecture with the metaphysics of dee
 p conscious breathing & slow motion\, yogic breathwork\, mantra/sound/vibr
 ation\, mudra\, subtle & contemplative practices.\nYoga Vinyasa Krama is a
  comprehensive hatha-raja yogic system for purification\, developing conce
 ntration\, neuromuscular fitness and conditioning\, refining & mastering t
 he breath\, awakening subtle energy and stilling the mind. Based on deep b
 reathing & the subtle movement of prana directed into the cartilage tissue
 \, sinuous musculature\, internal organs\, nerve pathways and nadis. It ha
 s over 700 intelligently sequenced slow\, conscious breath powered with pr
 ecision movement variations with pause (vinyasas)\, exploring many aesthet
 ic variations of each posture to correctly establish the main asanas while
  the mind merges with the breath.\nIncludes the energetics of drishti\, pr
 atikriyas\, bandha\, vaseth\, mudra\, mantra\, surya & ding namaskar with 
 breath & mantra\, cleansing kriyas\, Himalayan pranayama including includi
 ng ujjayi variations\, heating & cooling breaths\, solar\, lunar & soli-lu
 nar nadi shuddhi practices\, pranava & samantraka pranayama\, pratyahara\,
  subtle & contemplative practices in 12 kramas (sequences).\nThe whole pro
 cess gradually transforms the body and mind\, releasing old patterns of ph
 ysical and mental tension and dysfunctional patterns of movement\, providi
 ng tonic\, energetic and psychophysiological effects.\nThis system is pres
 ented from the teachings **Srivatsa Ramaswami** learned through his over 3
 3 years of one on one study with **Sri Krishnamacharya** and teachings fro
 m a similar **Himalayan method**.\nThis ongoing class will explore the ent
 ire system of 12 Kramas with each class focusing on a particular krama (se
 quence) & pranayama & contemplative practices.\nPlease practice on an empt
 y stomach. Morning beverage ok but please take it 30min or more before cla
 ss.\n***Certain injuries & health issues may be contraindicated Please con
 tact me if you have a concern***\nKnowledge of Correct Ujjayi Breathing re
 commended\n**$25 Drop In\, Discounted Class Passes\, Sliding Scale Availab
 le**\n\\*\\***RSVP Only** Contact Kara @707-235-1413\, [sunyogadance@gmail
 .com](http://sunyogadance@gmail.com%2A%2A/)**om**
